# RAG Pipeline

## Architecture

Custom implementation (no LangChain/LlamaIndex). Five modules in `backend/src/app/rag/`:

- `chunker.py` — parse files (PDF/DOCX/MD), split into chunks (800 tokens, 100 overlap)
- `embedder.py` — Qwen Embedding API via httpx
- `retriever.py` — Qdrant search (top_k=5, score_threshold=0.7)
- `llm.py` — Qwen 3.6 API streaming via httpx (OpenAI-compatible)
- `pipeline.py` — orchestration: embed -> search -> prompt -> stream

## Key Rules

- Always check relevance scores: if all chunks score below `RAG_SCORE_THRESHOLD`, return "no data" message
- System prompt must instruct LLM to answer only from provided context and cite sources
- Stream tokens via SSE with events: `token`, `sources`, `done`
- All external API calls (Qwen, Qdrant) must have timeout and error handling
- Use config values from Settings, never hardcode thresholds or model names
